Naval Station Norfolk Building NH94 generators #NH94-1A, NH94-2A, NH94-3A, NH94-4A.  The units were operated under conditions not defined as emergencies according to applicable regulations.  The NH-94 generators operate whenever there is a chance of power outage.  The Navy was issued a WL in July 2017 for the issue.  However the WL limit of 90 days 'expired' on October 26, 2017.  The Navy was not able to come into compliance.  The Navy was aware that an NOV and Consent Order are the next steps for a compliance plan for the Navy to obtain funding to address the issue.
-NOV issued 11/06/17.  The Navy civil service representative responded the same day;
-Navy to provide additional information on corrective action;
-02-03-21: NOV still open pending successful compliance testing of the generators.  Expected 1st qtr 2021.  Not expecting to proceed with CSO.
06-15-21: Case closed.
